div.p: Every year, there are worse and worse wildfires across the world. These fires are a great danger not only to the ecosystems they burn but also to the human firefighters who heroically combat them. One of the methods firefighters use to douse the flames is Aerial Firefighting in which an airplane or helicopter drops water or fire-retardant chemicals onto the fire.

p.span: We propose that this can be accomplished by drones, keeping human pilots out of danger for this particular task. Our system is a drone management system designed for use in combatting forest fires. It allows a user to specify locations with water and locations with fire, and order drones to take water to a fire.

tr.td:
The fire chief can manually deploy drones by designating
an area for drones to pick up water and another area to
drop the water using a FireFightOrder. They can also
recall drones using a RecallOrder.

Confirmation that the command was received, list of
